<paragraph id="991B9A143542FFE2FF0C8EDF5149D41F" blockId="12.[166,1225,541,895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">
Remarks. Casually recorded in 1983, this species was recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843542FFE2FBCD8EDF51A1D5FA" box="[1050,1188,672,699]" name="Switzerland" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E53542FFE2FF718EBF543CD59A" author="Merz, B." box="[166,313,704,731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" pagination="55 - 57" refId="ref12400" refString="Merz, B. 1991. Rhagoletis completa Cresson und Rhagoletis indifferens Curran, zwei wirtschaftlich bedeutende nordamerikanische nordamerikanische Fruchtfliegen neu fur Europa. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 64, 55 - 57." type="journal article" year="1991">Merz (1991)</bibRefCitation>
as “ 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FEBB8EBE5703D59B" authorityName=": Merz" authorityYear="1991" box="[364,518,704,731]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indifferens">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FEBB8EBE547BD59B" box="[364,382,705,730]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FE5B8EBF5703D59B" box="[396,518,704,730]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">indifferens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, but later was correctly identified as 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FC108EBE5156D59B" authorityName=": Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[967,1107,704,731]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FC108EBE56DCD59B" box="[967,985,705,730]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FC308EBF5156D59B" box="[999,1107,704,730]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">cingulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E53542FFE2FBB48EBF5428D5BD" author="Boller, E. F. &amp; Mani, E." pageId="12" pageNumber="465" pagination="83" refId="ref10645" refString="Boller, E. F. &amp; Mani, E., 1994. Two North American Rhagoletis spp. in Europe. IOBC / wprs Bulletin, 17, 83." type="journal article" year="1994">Boller &amp; Mani, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E53542FFE2FEE08E9E54C2D5BD" author="EPPO" box="[311,455,737,764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" pagination="8" refId="ref11070" refString="EPPO. 2004. Rhagoletis cingulata occurs in the Netherlands, but not R. indifferens. EPPO Reporting Service, 6 (87), 8." type="journal article" year="2004">EPPO, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E53542FFE2FE068E9E571BD5BD" author="EPPO" box="[465,542,737,764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" pagination="4 - 5" refId="ref11098" refString="EPPO. 2010 a. Rhagoletis cingulata occurs in Switzerland, but not R. indifferens. EPPO Reporting Service, 7 (127), 4 - 5." type="journal article" year="2010">2010 a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E53542FFE2FDFE8E9E5640D5BD" author="Merz, B. &amp; Korneyev, V. A." box="[553,837,737,764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" refId="ref12578" refString="Merz, B., Korneyev, V. A. 2004. Tephritidae. Fauna Europaea, version 1.1, http: // www. faunaeur. org (accessed 6.05.2016)." type="book" year="2004">Merz &amp; Korneyev, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). European specimens often have widely darkened mid and hind femora, as well as the wing pattern typical for 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FBFD8F7C51C7D45D" authorityName=": Merz" authorityYear="1991" box="[1066,1218,770,797]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indifferens">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FBFD8F7C5139D45D" box="[1066,1084,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FB9F8F7D51C7D45D" box="[1096,1218,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">indifferens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Available barcoding data of European specimens (J. Smit, unpublished data) fit well to existing COI sequences for 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FE3F8F3B5776D41C" authorityName=": Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[488,627,835,862]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FE3F8F3B54FFD41C" box="[488,506,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FDD08F3C5776D41C" box="[519,627,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">cingulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FCDC8F3B56A1D41C" authorityName=": Merz" authorityYear="1991" box="[779,932,835,862]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indifferens">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FCDC8F3B5618D41C" box="[779,797,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FCFD8F3C56A1D41C" box="[810,932,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">indifferens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on GenBank.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="991B9A143542FFE2FF0C8F1A514AD43E" blockId="12.[166,1225,541,895]" box="[219,1103,868,895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973542FFE2FF0C8F1A5463D43F" authorityName=": Loew" authorityYear="1873" box="[219,358,868,895]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FF0C8F1A55E8D43F" box="[219,237,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD046063542FFE2FF2D8F1B5463D43F" box="[250,358,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">cingulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a quarantine species, which is expected to spread to 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843542FFE2FC3F8F1B514ED43E" box="[1000,1099,868,895]" name="Ukraine" pageId="12" pageNumber="465">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
